    "reasoning": "To implement the Moore state machine as specified, I first analyze the state transition table to determine the states and their transitions. There are four states (A, B, C, D) with defined next states and outputs. I define the states using localparam for clarity. Next, I create the state register and implement the state transition logic using a combinational block that determines the next state based on the current state and input. Then I implement the output logic, which is a function of the current state. For the asynchronous reset, I ensure that the state register is reset to state A immediately when areset is high, regardless of the clock. Finally, I make sure that all sequential logic uses positive edge triggered clocking and that the reset is handled properly.",
    "module": "module TopModule (\n    input clk,\n    input areset,\n    input in,\n    output out\n);\n\n    // Define states\n    localparam STATE_A = 2'b00;\n    localparam STATE_B = 2'b01;\n    localparam STATE_C = 2'b10;\n    localparam STATE_D = 2'b11;\n\n    // State register\n    logic [1:0] state, state_next;\n\n    // Next state and output combinational logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        case (state)\n            STATE_A: state_next = (in) ? STATE_B : STATE_A;\n            STATE_B: state_next = (in) ? STATE_B : STATE_C;\n            STATE_C: state_next = (in) ? STATE_D : STATE_A;\n            STATE_D: state_next = (in) ? STATE_B : STATE_C;\n        endcase\n    end\n\n    // Output logic\n    always @(*) begin\n        case (state)\n            STATE_A: out = 1'b0;\n            STATE_B: out = 1'b0;\n            STATE_C: out = 1'b0;\n            STATE_D: out = 1'b1;\n        endcase\n    end\n\n    // Sequential logic\n    always @(posedge clk or posedge areset) begin\n        if (areset)\n            state <= STATE_A;\n        else\n            state <= state_next;\n    end\n\nendmodule"
}
